Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.27,0:00:40.80,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On May 3rd, 1956, 30,000 executive staff members from across Japan gathered
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.80,0:00:46.96,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the International Stadium in Ryogoku for the 14th Spring Headquarters General Meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:46.96,0:00:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism is a battle \Nbetween Buddha and the demons.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.83,0:00:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In your life, three obstacles and four demons \Nwill block your path to enlightenment,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:56.47,0:00:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,while from the outside, \Nthe three formidable enemies
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.29,0:01:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,will work to keep you \Nfrom fulfilling the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.86,0:01:05.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the Soka Gakkai's Director \Nof Public Relations, Yamamoto Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.67,0:01:10.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was already gearing everyone up \Nfor the nationwide July battle,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:10.89,0:01:15.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,hinting at the rise of the three formidable enemies spoken of in the Scriptures.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.85,0:01:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Under President Toda Josei's leadership \Nfirmly at the helm of the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:21.02,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s face the three \Nformidable enemies head-on,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:25.00,0:01:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,fortify our ever-growing faith \Nand arm ourselves with it,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:28.51,0:01:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to further our cause boldly \Nand with unity of minds!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.45,0:01:37.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi's warnings that day proved true \Nsooner than anyone could expect.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.37,0:01:41.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Starting in May in Osaka, the three obstacles, four demons, and three formidable enemies
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.85,0:01:44.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,from across the country \Nlaunched a fierce battle
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.56,0:01:47.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,against the Soka Gakkai—\Nand even among themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.40,0:02:09.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've not been in Osaka for three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.92,0:02:13.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,This time, though, I'm here to stay—\Nprobably right through July.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.43,0:02:17.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,The time has come for the decisive battle \Nthat will determine my future as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.62,0:02:22.75,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Starting with today's Sakai branch executives' meeting, we'll be gathering daily.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.75,0:02:28.09,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,But we also have to make time for one-on-one dialogue—that’s our top priority.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.09,0:02:31.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Without it, we can't keep the balance between the whole and individual.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.89,0:02:35.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,To help our comrades in Kansai soar,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.70,0:02:38.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,we need to spend time \Ngiving them solid one-on-one guidance.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.38,0:02:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This passage teaches us that everything hinges on the leader's determination.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.70,0:03:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With just one great person as a leader, \Neveryone under him becomes a hero.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.28,0:03:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Many roundtable discussions \Nin each district are scheduled for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.21,0:03:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of the roundtable, \Nregardless of the area,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.99,0:03:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,depends entirely on the determination of the host, the central figure.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.93,0:03:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep this in mind as you inspire peace and courage in your comrades.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.74,0:03:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do that?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.95,0:03:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.89,0:03:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's go over today's agenda once more \Nand identify the goals for each of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.30,0:03:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.63,0:03:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you. \NOnly two more places.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.53,0:03:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes ten places total today.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.32,0:03:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Ten places.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.08,0:03:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.98,0:03:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your daily hard work, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.83,0:03:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you agree? \NLife is faith, and faith is life. {oneness (of two opposing things); inseparability​in Buddhism}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.78,0:03:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything going well?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.74,0:04:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like a busy man. \NDid you take a day off today? {actually just "the man yonder" but that's too random}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.89,0:04:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.90,0:04:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... Are you unemployed? {/resting}{honestly unsure what's the difference here and in previous lines or what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.11,0:04:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Since work wasn't going well,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.58,0:04:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured I'd earn some good karma by lending you a hand instead. {fukuun = happiness and good fortune - not sure what he means, maybe karma, maybe he expects some actual reward like a position of power? then it's a simple "improve my fortunes"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.77,0:04:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't trust people who don't work!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.94,0:04:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.15,0:04:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.71,0:04:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin’s Dharma plainly warns us \Nnot to put our trust in loiterers.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.47,0:04:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're hung up on work troubles, you won't be able to fully devote yourself to faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.94,0:04:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{Right...}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.56,0:04:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The true faith \Nis much more rigorous than that.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.26,0:04:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin had this to say about it:
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.94,0:04:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.04,0:04:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...among other things.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.18,0:04:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He warns us sternly, that "To believe means to value life and be diligent in your work."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.19,0:04:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea you can just wash your hands of it \Nand leave everything for faith to sort out
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.72,0:05:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,contradicts Daishonin's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.68,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now’s the time to grit our teeth \Nand push forward,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.85,0:05:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,giving our all to both work and faith, \Nno matter how tough it gets.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.04,0:05:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you agree, friend?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.16,0:05:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand now. \NI'll make sure to return to my job!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.77,0:05:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have any paper and brushes here?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.25,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we do.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.72,0:05:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us commemorate this meeting \Nwith a piece of calligraphy. {writing (esp. commissioned calligraphy); drawing; painting}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.38,0:05:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yeah! or maybe Huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.75,0:05:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.92,0:05:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! {/Wow! }
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.17,0:05:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.05,0:05:47.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi truly was everywhere at once. {appearing in unexpected places and at unexpected moments; elusive; phantom}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.66,0:05:50.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He spent his days making the rounds of bases
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.03,0:05:52.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and his evenings \Nattending roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.77,0:06:00.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Wherever and whenever he went, Shinichi stirred up a whirlwind of propagation in his wake.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.57,0:06:04.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He won people over with his gentle, \Nwarm and considerate tone.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.61,0:06:07.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Shinichi’s words \Nbrimmed with conviction,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.76,0:06:11.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,inspiring most newcomers \Nto eagerly step up and join the fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.44,0:06:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do a good job!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.62,0:06:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d love to stay and chat longer, \Nbut sadly, I have to go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.80,0:06:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I really can't keep the men's division \Nwaiting any longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.97,0:06:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.66,0:06:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.15,0:06:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Take care, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.93,0:06:35.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After the men's division meeting, Shinichi was on his way to the Kansai headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.86,0:06:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya-kun, the men's division is also fired up.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.41,0:06:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you very much. They take to propagating with incredible vigor these days!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.74,0:06:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And when their efforts bear fruit, they become all the more fired up to give it their best!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.16,0:06:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, so I thought. \NHuh? Oya-kun,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.04,0:06:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it the roundtable here still in progress? {unsure, maybe it's a statement, maybe he means "we're going to another roundtable today?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.62,0:06:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably over.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.97,0:07:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter. Even if it's just one or two people left, let's meet them
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.82,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and lift their spirits.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.56,0:07:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.78,0:07:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.38,0:07:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Who might this be? \NThat voice sounds familiar.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.51,0:07:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon the late visit. \NYamamoto here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.95,0:07:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.27,0:07:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice work, as always.  \NIs the roundtable already wrapped up?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.43,0:07:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we closed it not long ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.71,0:07:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it productive?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.05,0:07:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We had six people \Nwant to join this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.97,0:07:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great! \NI expected no less from you.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.91,0:07:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, no matter how far you go, \Ndon't stop believing in your path.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.01,0:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that one day, \Nyou'll fulfill the lives of your dreams!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.71,0:07:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.67,0:07:43.94,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,This morning, before dawn had even broken, \Nan unexpected incident occurred in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.94,0:07:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a corner room on the second floor. \NYou'll go down the hall.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.48,0:07:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll watch the stairs over there. \NYou stay here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.70,0:07:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.93,0:07:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.81,0:07:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who might that be so early?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.20,0:07:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.44,0:08:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,South Police Station.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.23,0:08:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We have questions about \Nthe Lotus Temple incident.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.82,0:08:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still investigating that? {そりゃまた何ですねん!?}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.74,0:08:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We need you at the police station right now. {/would like to accompany you to the ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.01,0:08:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.34,0:08:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.62,0:08:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. \NThere's probably been a mix-up.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.95,0:08:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, ma'am, please tell \NManager Sagawa what happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.54,0:08:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The police had some follow-up questions about the Lotus Temple incident.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.13,0:08:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. I will!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.50,0:08:30.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,What the hell? I came along voluntarily, \Nyet they're acting like I'm some big-time criminal!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.01,0:08:32.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Something's off...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.99,0:08:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The Lotus Temple incident?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.31,0:08:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, that's not right!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.06,0:08:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The police probably dragged him out of his house \Nbecause of his ties to Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.19,0:08:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's report straight to Chief Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.86,0:08:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.97,0:08:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it. Thank you. Please tell me at once \Nif there are further developments.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.47,0:09:00.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,This makes six of our men... Weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.00,0:09:04.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,All six were brought in for questioning \Nat approximately the same time.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.31,0:09:06.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,It can't be a coincidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.34,0:09:10.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,All under the pretext of rehashing \Na long-resolved incident...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.68,0:09:12.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's their play here?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.93,0:09:17.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's worse, if the media reports \Nall these police roundups side by side, {/summons/apprehensions}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.87,0:09:20.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,it’ll inevitably hurt Soka Gakkai’s reputation.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.06,0:09:23.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.00,0:09:27.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,All six people taken in for questioning \Nthis morning were our devoted champions.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.71,0:09:33.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,With all those men in police custody at once, \Nthe rest of the branch is bound to be restless.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.75,0:09:43.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it. \NThe first demon has made an appearance.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.52,0:09:47.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,Terrified by our fierce stand in the Battle for Kansai,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.02,0:09:49.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,the demon army \Nfinally launched its counterattack.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.82,0:09:53.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On this day, Toda happened to be in Osaka, \Ngiving a lecture on Scriptures.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.87,0:09:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I must apologize.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.49,0:10:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Six members of the Osaka Branch were taken in \Nfor questioning by the police this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.33,0:10:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What? On what charges?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.17,0:10:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ostensibly, assault and battery.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.73,0:10:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They told one of them it's about the Lotus Temple incident a year and three months ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.88,0:10:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our men's division executives \Nwere present there.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.53,0:10:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one where the head priest \Nof the Lotus Temple refused to meet with us,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.33,0:10:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so they intercepted him on his way to a memorial service to try and talk to him, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.56,0:10:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We still need to talk! \NPlease wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.09,0:10:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think I have anything \Nto talk about with lowlifes like you? {ill-bred; vulgar; boorish}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.49,0:10:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.99,0:10:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.32,0:10:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, after that...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.26,0:10:41.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi explained each of the incidents \Nthat led up to the police summons...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.95,0:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these are minor incidents \Nthat have nothing to do with assault and battery.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.03,0:10:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And yet, the authorities have set up an investigation HQ at South Police Station.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.27,0:10:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What? But isn't it completely out of proportion? {/isn't it a strange story}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.13,0:11:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and what's more bizarre \Nis that this article appeared in the morning paper.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.63,0:11:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"After six months of undercover investigation, \Nthe Osaka Prefectural Police Security Division
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.09,0:11:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,obtained arrest warrants for six individuals \Nfrom the Osaka District Court.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.19,0:11:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A mass arrest will be conducted, \Noverseen by the chief of security."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.01,0:11:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this is a warning article? {(advance) notice; preliminary announcement; warning article - idk what he means, either that the publishers were in cahoots with police and knew about the whole thing before the arrests happened somehow (most likely version), or that it's a warning to those who were to be arrested, so the police had to move in now before everyone saw the article}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.10,0:11:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.66,0:11:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only about 6 a.m. \Nwhen all six were apprehended.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.52,0:11:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This article had to be prepared in advance.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.06,0:11:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you think the police \Nare deliberately targeting us?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.38,0:11:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's the only explanation.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.84,0:11:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they trying to paint Soka Gakkai \Nas a violent religious organization
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.84,0:11:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by dredging up minor \Nand long-resolved incidents?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.82,0:11:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. The unrest among members \Nwill be a problem.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.02,0:11:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Osaka, which is in a thrill right now, cannot be allowed to fall victim to the demons' schemes.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.69,0:11:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, as the saying goes, \N"Follow not, nor fear the demon."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.86,0:12:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We will fight back resolutely, \Nas Daishonin commanded us to.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.08,0:12:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it. We'll talk again \Nat tonight's Scriptures lecture.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.91,0:12:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is the crucial time for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.40,0:12:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.84,0:12:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen today's evening issue?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.50,0:12:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.72,0:12:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Too much faith leads to violence"—\Nquite the headline.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.78,0:12:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's also so fishy.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.77,0:12:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. I have never seen or heard \Nof a Soka Gakkai member resorting to violence.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.29,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It reeks fabrication.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.16,0:12:48.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,As expected, everyone \Nbrought with them the newspapers.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.69,0:12:53.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,They're all uneasy about six \Nof their comrades getting arrested.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.09,0:12:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us get started, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.25,0:12:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The chapter we'll be learning today \Nis "On omens." {瑞相御書}{/Zuiso Gosho}{translation from https://www.nichirenlibrary.org/en/wnd-1/Content/79}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.49,0:13:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"Strange occurrences in the heavens \Nastound all people,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and calamities on earth disturb everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.95,0:13:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Buddha \Nwas about to preach the Lotus Sutra,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.16,0:13:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he caused the five omens \Nand the six omens to appear."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.50,0:13:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.31,0:13:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Great events are always accompanied \Nby significant shocks. {lit: There is always something auspicious about things.}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.61,0:13:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There are strange occurrences in the heavens and calamities on earth that scare everyone,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.53,0:13:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is a reason for all of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.36,0:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When Shakyamuni Buddha \Nwas about to preach the Lotus Sutra,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.51,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it was preceded by a great omen, \Nthe only one in the 40-odd years.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.66,0:13:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is that the Lotus Sutra
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.77,0:13:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is the highest teaching, \Ncapable of even destroying original ignorance. {kinda like the original sin}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.61,0:13:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.34,0:13:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we've all been preaching the Lotus Sutra \Nand pushing the propagation work
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.14,0:13:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a bit more enthusiastically than usual\Nin the Kansai region. {not sure what he means tbh; このところ関西の地で皆さん方が少しばかり熱心に法華経を説き いささか活発に弘教活動をした}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.56,0:13:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done nothing wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.31,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the Latter Day of the Law, \Nthe arrival of the Lotus Sutra
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.92,0:13:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,must be marked by even more intense omens \Nthan in the Shakyamuni era.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.07,0:14:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you all know from today's morning and evening papers,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.47,0:14:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,an absurd situation came about in which the Osaka Police have arrested six of our comrades.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.54,0:14:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The charges are based on an incident that happened more than a year ago
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.82,0:14:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and had long been fully resolved.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.24,0:14:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're dredging it back up,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.01,0:14:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to spin the story \Nto make us look like the ones at fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.12,0:14:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't bend the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.58,0:14:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In due time, the truth will come to light,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.85,0:14:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and our six comrades \Nwill be freed without harm.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.43,0:14:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are hardships we must endure \Nfor our faith, and this is assuredly one of them. {これを信仰の上で受けねばならない難といえば まさに難であります}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.44,0:14:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say this is an honorable hardship borne in the name of the Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.53,0:14:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to be frank with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.22,0:14:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The newspapers waste no time painting Soka Gakkai as violent religious fanatics.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.65,0:15:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But you tell me—when and where did we ever use violence to enforce our faith?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.05,0:15:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone here was foolish enough to spread faith through violence, step forward now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.88,0:15:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The newspapers made a business \Nout of writing one-sided stories,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.25,0:15:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,deciding right and wrong with a flick of a pen \Nwithout ever seeking the truth—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.45,0:15:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that the real violence?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.28,0:15:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my opinion. \NWhat do you all think?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.76,0:15:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.56,0:15:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai stands alone \Nin this Latter Day of the Law
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.21,0:15:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as the sole organization faithfully practicing Nichiren Daishonin’s Buddhism
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.62,0:15:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just as he originally taught it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.94,0:15:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Our only wish is to rid this world of such words as "suffering" and "unhappiness" altogether! {私たちが願うところは この世から“悲惨”という二字を 不幸という不幸を 一切なくすことにあります!}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,However, no sooner had everyone began working devotedly for the Common Path
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.60,0:15:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,than the government suddenly lashed out,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.91,0:16:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,much like the Kamakura Shogunate that persecuted Nichiren Daishonin 700 years ago,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.41,0:16:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,arresting six Soka Gakkai members on trumped-up charges and tired old slanders.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.67,0:16:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But we mustn't flinch an inch!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.95,0:16:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With tonight’s chapter \Nof the Scriptures in mind,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.81,0:16:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m convinced that this incident is an auspicious omen, heralding a great victory for us in Kansai!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.38,0:16:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to leave for Kochi tomorrow, \Nbut the next few days will decide everything.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.08,0:16:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, you've done well.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.78,0:16:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make a step away from Osaka \Nuntil everyone is safely released.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.56,0:16:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that was the plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.04,0:16:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many days it takes, \NI won't leave Kansai.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.17,0:16:50.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,From the Buddhist point of view, it is clear that this incident is the work of the demons.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.05,0:16:57.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, this was the first time that our Kansai member was arrested for his religious activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.45,0:17:00.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,What kind of effect will it have \Non the ongoing battle?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,In any case, I must keep chanting.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.29,0:17:05.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only way to defeat \Nthe demons is with faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.86,0:17:10.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,As the person in charge, \Nmy strong prayer will decide everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.26,0:17:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.06,0:17:21.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The next day,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:21.23,0:17:25.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi completed his scheduled tutoring rounds \Nduring the day, and then in the evening,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.64,0:17:29.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he went through the roundtables, \Noffering encouragement to the members.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.75,0:17:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.93,0:17:43.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,In spite of yesterday's news, the number of roundtable discussions held has not decreased.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.54,0:17:46.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,It did not shake their will to fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.21,0:17:47.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only problem now...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.84,0:17:49.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,The leaders from all over the country
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.62,0:17:54.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,report that the atmosphere at the roundtables \Nsuddenly became heavy. {lit: as many reports came - idk maybe there were more arrests elsewhere and people at roundtables got word of it so that's why}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.09,0:17:59.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,The shock of being arrested for your religious work is hard to express in words,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.29,0:18:02.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,but it probably affected their hearts deeply.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.46,0:18:05.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,Attack!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.21,0:18:08.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right, we'll be sitting ducks \Nif we try to play defense. {lit: we can't break through this situation with defense}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.67,0:18:11.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,Attack is the best defense!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.01,0:18:14.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,Only by going on the offensive can we seize our chance to win,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.05,0:18:17.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,and the sooner that happens, the better.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.78,0:18:57.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This morning, dispatched members from Tokyo
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.79,0:19:03.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and local executives gathered for an early morning lecture on the Scriptures as usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.60,0:19:10.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But there was a suffocating heaviness in the air \Nthat had never been there before.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.12,0:19:15.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi sensed at once what was causing it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.55,0:19:19.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable. Even the executive staff \Nfell under the demons' influence.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.95,0:19:21.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,The change must start here!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.37,0:19:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear the reports first.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.66,0:19:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the atmosphere like at last night's roundtable discussions? Anyone, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.63,0:19:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's hear from Ueda-kun, \Nthe dispatch executive.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.92,0:19:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Everyone was in good spirits,\Nbut we dispersed early last night
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.01,0:19:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No one brought up any specific questions \Nabout the recent incident,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.62,0:19:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seemed as though everyone \Nwas quite frightened on the inside.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.33,0:19:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I was prepared to answer any questions in full if they came up, but that opportunity never arose…
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.82,0:19:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one who is frightened?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.34,0:19:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.22,0:20:00.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,He’s right… \NDeep down, I’m getting cold feet too.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.18,0:20:03.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was scared just as much as everyone else!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.04,0:20:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Oral Teachings of the Buddha...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.00,0:20:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,...is the golden maxim.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.98,0:20:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We, who have been entrusted the Lotus Sutra, \Nmust accept the current difficulties as a given.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.26,0:20:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it would be presumptuous to suggest that they measure up
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.78,0:20:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hardships Nichiren Daishonin endured.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.47,0:20:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot expect to remain entirely unaffected{, to some extent,} \Nby the ignorance of lay people. {idk what he means: 凡夫のつたなさで大なり小なり影響を受けずには済みません}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.44,0:20:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Lightning fast: How to deal with this crisis and fight it is our biggest challenge right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.15,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Once, when one of his followers \Nwas in trouble, Daishonin said...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.85,0:20:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,...to lift his spirits.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.23,0:20:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"No matter how tough things get,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.78,0:20:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what may come, you must never \Nallow yourself the sin of cowardice.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.60,0:20:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your faith strong as much as you can."
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.47,0:21:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Daishonin \Nwould tell us if he was here now.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.99,0:21:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment you allow \Neven a trace of fear into your heart,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.73,0:21:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be sure you've let the demon defeat you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.27,0:21:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you need to cut off decisively.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.96,0:21:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What rests on our shoulders
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.19,0:21:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the weight of the happiness and misery\N of 45,000 Soka Gakkai households in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.52,0:21:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We must not treat lightly something
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.41,0:21:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that has brought long-awaited happiness \Nto so many of our comrades.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.37,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's the time to man up!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.41,0:21:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you intend to strike the demon down \Nwith the sword of your faith, now's the time!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.83,0:21:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's right! \NIt's now or never.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.51,0:21:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it! \NI can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.70,0:21:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Never fear or falter!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.97,0:21:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't lose!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.72,0:21:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The righteous Buddhism and the righteous faith \Nalways get the last laugh!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.66,0:21:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.60,0:21:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, muster your courage for this fight!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.54,0:21:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's show the rest of Osaka what the spirit of Kansai in Soka Gakkai members is capable of! {/Naniwa}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.90,0:22:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.29,0:22:11.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It goes without saying \Nthat from noon to night that day,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.12,0:22:14.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at roundtable discussions and meetings across Osaka,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.12,0:22:18.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi’s impassioned speech \Nduring the early morning lecture
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.57,0:22:23.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,kept everyone energized, \Nlike a torrent of life running right through the city.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:25.28,0:22:26.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In just a day,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.67,0:22:29.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Osaka had regained all of its momentum.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:30.10,0:22:34.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The sturdy organizational structure, \Nbuilt over five months,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.40,0:22:38.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,had proven strong and flexible enough \Nto withstand any challenge,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.34,0:22:41.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,both from within and without.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:42.11,0:22:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it, got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:44.55,0:22:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional results? {idk; 成果の追加ですか?}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.84,0:22:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.87,0:22:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure like to work hard!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:49.54,0:22:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 'cause all the group chiefs \Nare unstoppable!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.37,0:22:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I'm jealous!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.29,0:22:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We came here to chant together \Nto chant everyone up. {also idk; うちは皆が元気出すように題目を上げにきましてん}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:58.00,0:23:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great! \NGyo-san, do your best!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.32,0:23:06.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,What a huge change from yesterday!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:06.14,0:23:09.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,This morning's guidance from Yamamoto really brought Osaka back to life.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.64,0:23:13.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we'll see an even bigger spike in conversions this month!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.25,0:23:21.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Tokyo has certainly become more active \Nin roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.92,0:23:25.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,But it's merely a mechanical reaction. {unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.26,0:23:31.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,Tokyo doesn’t even come close \Nto matching the exhilaration of Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:31.62,0:23:36.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we’ll lose the battle before it even begins. Immediate action is needed.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.06,0:23:41.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soon after, it was announced that Tokyo \Nwould be changing commanders.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.55,0:23:45.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Director Ishikawa Yukio \Nwas appointed overall commander,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.80,0:23:52.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,while Ryoichi Sawada, whom he succeeded, \Nwas assigned to oversee only the Tokyo area.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.70,0:23:56.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, even with this change, \Nthe Tokyo area,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.88,0:24:03.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,once set on this course, ultimately couldn't break free from the path of inertia.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.06,0:24:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, so the district head \Nwent out to proselytize?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.02,0:24:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When he's back, please tell him \NYamamoto wanted to see him.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:20.58,0:24:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, give this to your dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:24.41,0:24:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? A young man \Nnamed Yamamoto came?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:27.41,0:24:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that could be Chief Yamamoto?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:29.82,0:24:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It might just be...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.86,0:24:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And he gave me this for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.79,0:24:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.62,0:24:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Check this out!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.27,0:24:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief tells me to leap into the battle \Nand fight like a lion! {師子奮迅の戦いをせい = impetous dash forward of a lion - don't really know what it means or where it came from; dunno what it says on his fan either}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.31,0:24:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet he doesn't know \Nhow sluggish our district is. {slump; lull}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.73,0:24:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:46.82,0:24:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I gotta do it now!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:48.47,0:24:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hesitate when he sics me like this, \Nwhat kind of man would I be?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:52.24,0:24:58.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The next day, this district head had become \Na changed man who fights with ferocity of a lion. {lit: lion's impetous dash forward district head}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:58.89,0:25:00.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was soon after this
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.67,0:25:05.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that he persuaded 33 people to join \Nduring a single district roundtable discussion.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:06.38,0:25:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.38,0:25:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, good evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:08.82,0:25:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How is your district doing?\NAll of our guys are keen as mustard.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:13.30,0:25:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here. We're unstoppable. Like a train!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:16.89,0:25:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, pardon.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:18.25,0:25:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta hurry, or they won't accept it.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.21,0:25:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew. Finally made it in time. \NWe got additional results!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.08,0:25:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:33.16,0:25:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,38 more households? \NYou did really well!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:37.81,0:25:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:39.62,0:25:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We got 400 in our area alone today!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:42.95,0:25:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what the overall branch result will come to.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:45.88,0:25:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only four days left until the deadline. \NBut it'll be one hella number for sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:52.01,0:25:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels as if the entire Kansai HQ
Dialogue: 10,0:25:53.84,0:25:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is sailing steadily ahead like a battleship to the rhythm of a military march.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.45,0:26:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:03.63,0:26:08.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The six members detained by the police \Nwere released one after another,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:08.25,0:26:13.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and by the afternoon of May 25, \Nall had returned to Kansai Headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:15.55,0:26:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're good!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:16.74,0:26:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:19.52,0:26:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, I'm back!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.83,0:26:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. \NCongratulations on your release.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:25.38,0:26:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:28.19,0:26:32.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The arrested members \Nalso immediately returned to the front line.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:32.78,0:26:38.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"The truth always wins in the end. \NAnd we will definitely prove that." {/the righteous one}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:38.79,0:26:43.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The flame of the members' fighting spirit \Ncould not be extinguished.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:43.67,0:26:46.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The battle of propagation \Nfinally picked up,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:46.73,0:26:52.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and Osaka buzzed with activists rushing between roundtable discussions and propagation efforts.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:52.53,0:26:54.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,New entries poured in without end,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:54.56,0:26:59.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the results continued to climb \Nwith no sign of stopping.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:59.54,0:27:01.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When finally...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:04.79,0:27:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the results \Nof conversion work in May!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:09.82,0:27:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,1st place: Osaka Branch, \N11,111 households!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:15.28,0:27:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.00,0:27:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:28.71,0:27:30.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:31.36,0:27:36.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is the fight of our comrades in Kansai \Nwho gritted their teeth and fought till the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:37.49,0:27:40.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,11,111 households—
Dialogue: 10,0:27:40.58,0:27:45.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,an unprecedented conversion result \Nthat nobody else would dare to dream of.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:45.21,0:27:49.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Under Yamamoto Shinichi’s leadership, \Nthe Osaka members
Dialogue: 10,0:27:49.07,0:27:51.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,have built an everlasting monument
Dialogue: 10,0:27:51.34,0:27:55.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that will shine with glory for all time in the history of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:55.44,0:28:00.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The strong foundation for the {\i1}Invincible Kansai{\i0} was laid here.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:04.92,0:28:09.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,This May, thanks to the great progress \Nof the Osaka branch,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:09.55,0:28:12.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,we were able to reach \Nnearly 30,000 households nationwide.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.61,0:28:16.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,But that also means greater repercussions. {だがそれだけ反動は大きく}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:16.49,0:28:20.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,Established religious groups and societal forces will continue
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.07,0:28:22.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,trying to frustrate \Nthe efforts of Soka Gakkai’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.85,0:28:27.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,And their attempts are certain \Nto grow even more intense from here on.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:32.42,0:28:35.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,We're finally approaching \Na steep mountain on our path.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:36.67,0:28:45.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,But no matter how steep and rough the way \Nmay be, Shinichi and I must overcome it together.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:45.93,0:28:51.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's to eliminate all unhappiness \Nand suffering from this world!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:51.18,0:28:54.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After this, Toda composed a poem.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:04.66,0:29:08.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This poem was brimming with the warmth \Nof the teacher-student bond
Dialogue: 10,0:29:08.41,0:29:13.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,between Toda Josei and Yamamoto Shinichi, along with their unwavering determination.
